column5: I'm selecting books for my classroom library before I send out the fliers to students.

I am disappointed that in the flyer the price for a book is listed in big letters for $12 and then in little writing that it jumps in price after a certain date.  The price of a book should not change within the same order time frame of a book order. My kid was saving up for that book, and then a little shocked when we went to order and the price was more expensive then what he saw in the flyer.
The site was not registering my student orders.
I am annoyed that I earned $10 to spend but aren’t allowed to spend it until May.

My son has be reading all of the Press Start series that he can get his hands on.  I noticed tonight that it was published by Scholastic so I came online to check for it in the book orders.  Found the newest one in the series right away, and then found a link to a 6 book set.  I'm not ordering it today only because I want to wait to see if son's class does another round of book orders before the end of the year.  If not, I will be back to order them soon.
I will be ordering a book soon. This visit was just to see the wish list and share it with the other parents.
Bring back $1 books without stipulations, they should be available for students to buy.
It’s difficult to use on a phone
Except that I was  interrupted in looking to take this survey! That was kind of annoying, now can I get back to looking?

Hard to find the wish list, I wish it would state look up top to see wish list. Other than that it was fine.

Unable to send an invite letter to a new teacher

the website in general is confusing and not user friendly, plus the selection is not that great.
the website in general is confusing and not user friendly, plus the selection is not that great.

I just submitted an order earlier this week and it is not showing any of the orders that I've submitted this week.  Lately, the site hasn't been showing anything about orders when I use my computer at school.  I have to go home and use my computer at home to submit or check orders.

Just sometimes when I hit back button it would take me to the first page of the category I was looking at instead of just previous screen so looking at book detail that I found on page 6, hit back button and it would take you back to the books on page 1 in the list
I would order more if there was a larger selection and you could actually read a little bit of the quick looks.
I really dislike the sliding bar to the right when I scroll down to view titles. Sometimes it gets stuck and I can't move it.

How do I know an order has been submitted online. I would like to be notified if I have an order that is waiting to be approved.  I will check my trash to see if the emails aren't coming through.  I need some kind of notification.
I received a damaged book and wanted to share a photo with you.  It is not easy to get an email to you.  I am hoping for a quick response and easy and fast replacement.
I received a damaged book and wanted to share a photo with you.  It is not easy to get an email to you.  I am hoping for a quick response and easy and fast replacement.
website seems a bit outdated but it still gets the job done.

I didn't have any trouble I want to wait another day before I put in my order

I wish I could see the prices besides just on the flyers. I entered my teacher's code but still had to sign in to see prices!? Not very continent for browsing to see if I want to purchase

I was only upset because I wanted to add The Sour Grape to our order and wanted soft cover and it is only available in hard cover. My son wants the whole series but they are all soft cover so we want them to be the same and also don't want to spend the $$ on hardcover so we had to skip it this time.

I also think this would increase the online sales. Your search engine needs some help.

And recently someone pointed out to me how this might discourage reading for kids who can't afford the book fairs and see friends buying books that can't. Some children may feel unworthy of reading. I would be willing to donate toward that as a parent who is able to buy children books.

I just wanted to say that I will be retiring after teaching and using Scholastic for 32 years.  I spent  the first 18 years of my career teaching 2nd grade and 1 teaching 4th before moving to 6th grade.  In each of these positions, I have sent home your flyers and had many, many students purchase.
